{"author":{"id":"5e53c9bce7eeb69e347743575f6133426338c29498e200aa8bf1bef46209d02a"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1433432418,"nonce":"3qRtVxtDkm2qlmya1DQbVuApKX4=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDEwODkzOTQ4OA==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/168#issuecomment-108939488"},"message":"I'm not going to be the roadblock, +1 for dropping. =)\n\nHowever, could we discuss the idea of adding requirements meta-tags that can imply something like \"requires OpenSSL (and not just the runtime, we need the headers too)\". That way, down the line, if granted permission by the Galaxy admin, Galaxy could `sudo apt-get install openssl-dev` / `sudo yum install openssl-devel` / etc. prior to attempting installation. Or perhaps this isn't necessary if we are ultimately moving dependencies outside of the TS.\n\nWhat I'd like to avoid is \"losing\" the knowledge of what packages depend on what things, it makes for a more difficult user experience when someone goes to install something from the TS and it fails for reasons that are unclear to anyone not seasoned in compiling software.","files":null}]}